# D Proofs
## D. 1 Proof of Proposition(1)

The proof is by induction. First we prove the statement for the base case with only one source, that is $\bar{A}=2$. This collapses to the normal case of Bayesian updating with conjugate normal prior, therefore we have:

$$
\begin{aligned}
\mu_{P} & =\frac{\mu_{1} \sigma_{0}^{2}+\mu_{0} \sigma_{1}^{2}}{\sigma_{0}^{2}+\sigma_{1}^{2}} \\
\sigma_{P}^{2} & =\frac{\sigma_{0}^{2} \sigma_{1}^{2}}{\sigma_{0}^{2}+\sigma_{1}^{2}}
\end{aligned}
$$

Then we prove that if the statement holds for a generic set A with $\bar{A}=n$, then it holds also for B with $\bar{B}=n+1$. If the statement holds for $\bar{A}=n$, and receive an extra source of information, the new posterior distribution has parameters:

$$
\begin{aligned}
\mu_{P}=\frac{\mu_{K+1} \frac{\prod_{j=0}^{K} \sigma_{j}^{2}}{\sum|A|^{A-1}}+\frac{\sum_{k=0}^{K}\left(\mu_{k} \cdot|A|_{k}^{\bar{A}-1}\right)}{\sum|A|^{A-1}}}{\frac{\prod_{j=0}^{K} \sigma_{j}^{2}}{\sum|A|^{A-1}}+\sigma_{K+1}^{2}}=\frac{\frac{\sum_{k=0}^{K+1}\left(\mu_{k} \cdot\left[A \cup \sigma_{K+1}^{2}\right]_{k}^{\bar{A}}\right)}{\sum|A|^{A-1}}}{\frac{\prod_{j=0}^{K} \sigma_{j}^{2}}{\sum|A|^{A-1}}+\frac{\sum\left[\left[A \cup \sigma_{K+1}^{2}\right]^{\bar{A}} \cup \prod_{j=0}^{K} \sigma_{j}^{2}\right]}{\sum|A|^{A-1}}}= \\
=\frac{\sum_{k=0}^{K+1}\left(\mu_{k} \cdot\left[A \cup \sigma_{K+1}^{2}\right]_{k}^{\bar{A}}\right)}{\sum\left[A \cup \sigma_{K+1}^{2}\right]^{\bar{A}}}
\end{aligned}
$$

$$
\sigma_{P}^{2}=\frac{\frac{\prod_{j=0}^{K} \sigma_{j}^{2}}{\sum|A|^{4-1}} \sigma_{K+1}^{2}}{\frac{\prod_{j=0}^{K} \sigma_{j}^{2}}{\sum|A|^{4-1}}}+\sigma_{K+1}^{2}=\frac{\frac{\prod_{j=0}^{K+1} \sigma_{j}^{2}}{\sum|A|^{4-1}}}{\frac{\prod_{j=0}^{K} \sigma_{j}^{2}}{\sum|A|^{4-1}}}+\frac{\sum\left[\left[A_{i} \sigma_{K+1}^{2}\right]^{A} \backslash \prod_{j=0}^{K} \sigma_{j}^{2}\right]}{\sum|A|^{4-1}}}=\frac{\prod_{j=0}^{K+1} \sigma_{j}^{2}}{\sum\left[A \cup \sigma_{K+1}^{2}\right]^{A}}
$$

Therefore we have:

$$
\begin{gathered}
\mu_{P}=\frac{\sum_{k=0}^{K+1}\left(\mu_{k} \cdot[B]_{k}^{\bar{B}-1}\right)}{\sum[B]^{\bar{B}-1}} \\
\sigma_{P}^{2}=\frac{\prod_{j=0}^{K+1} \sigma_{j}^{2}}{\sum[B]^{\bar{B}-1}}
\end{gathered}
$$

which are the posterior mean and variance for the set $B=A \cup \sigma_{K+1}^{2}$ with $\bar{B}=\bar{A}+1=$ $n+1$, hence concluding the proof.
